#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:1
msgid "VTK::IOFLUENTCFF"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:3
msgid "This page describes the Fluent CFF IO functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:5
msgid "vtkFLUENTCFFReader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:6
msgid ""
"Provide a reader for the FluentCFF file format. Provide the Fluent CFF "
"Reader (Common Fluid Format)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:9
msgid ""
"The reader supports cartesian grid, unstructured grid (poly, tetra, ...), "
"3D/2D, double and single precision files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:12
msgid ""
"Similarly to the legacy reader (`vtkFLUENTReader`), the Fluent CFF reader "
"requires two files: the case file (`.cas.h5`) and the data file (`.dat.h5`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:15
msgid "The Fluent CFF readers uses the HDF library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:17
msgid ""
"It is worth noting that the Fluent CFF file format is the default format in "
"the latest Fluent version and that ANSYS no longer uses the legacy binary or "
"ASCII formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:21
msgid ""
"Developed by Arthur Piquet and based on the vtkFLUENTReader class from Brian "
"W. Dotson &"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/IO/FLUENTCFF/README.md:22
msgid "Acknowledgments"
msgstr ""

